</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #2c5b53;'>Economy &amp; Labor</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/postal-workers-union-leader-warns-the-usps-could-be-dead-in-three-months/">Postal Workers Union Leader Warns the USPS Could Be Dead in Three Months</a>
</article>
</div>
</aside>
</div>
<div class="entry-content primary-content-column columns small-12 medium-8">
<p>The final Democratic presidential debate of 2020 was a dispiriting affair for reasons that went far beyond the politics of it. The specter of COVID-19 lent a stark gloominess to the occasion, as did the seeming emptiness of the room itself: three <em>CNN</em> moderators, two men and the cameras. I never thought I&rsquo;d miss a debate audience, but the energy was gone from that room, and the brightly lit set could not make up for it.</p>
<p>And then there&rsquo;s this: &ldquo;The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention recommended that events of 50 people or more not be held for about two months,&rdquo; <em>Bloomberg News</em> <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-15/cdc-says-gatherings-over-50-people-should-be-delayed-eight-weeks">reported</a> on Sunday. &ldquo;For the next eight weeks, organizers should cancel or postpone in-person events of that size throughout the U.S.&rdquo;</p>
<p>Primaries are scheduled to be held on Tuesday in Arizona, Ohio, Illinois and Florida. These contests were set to be decisive before the CDC&rsquo;s recommendation &mdash; if Joe Biden wins them all, his delegate lead over Bernie Sanders would become all but insurmountable &mdash; and may be all the more so now. These four primaries could be the last of the season. Georgia has postponed its primary, which was slated for next Tuesday, and Louisiana&rsquo;s April 4 primary has likewise been delayed.</p><div class="truth-post-content-high  inline-callout-container" id="truth-255792"><aside class=" callout inline-callout callout--subscribe callout--dark" id="truth-255395">
<h2>Uncompromised, uncompromising news</h2>
<p>Get reliable, independent news and commentary delivered to your inbox every day.</p>
